mutant: m008_header_offset_byteslice
target: segment/header.go
failure-mode: |
  BlockIndexOffset is encoded into buf[89:97] instead of buf[90:98], shifting
  the field one byte and corrupting the adjacent header field. Models an
  off-by-one in a hand-maintained fixed-offset header layout.
expected-detection: |
  Reopening/decoding a sealed segment should fail (bad offset / checksum), so
  ObserveSegments errors out and the harness fails. Default tier.
expected-tier: default
tiers: default,stress

